lookgoodr, an obituary
</h1>
<hr />

<p>This was the biggest project that I‚Äôve undertaken in a while, and it honestly didn‚Äôt turn out that great ü§° Consider this an obituary to the incredibly-named <strong>lookgoodr</strong>:</p>

<p><a href="https://lookgoodr.herokuapp.com/" target="_blank">
    <img src="http://localhost:4000/assets/lookgoodr/home-1.PNG" /></a></p>

<p><br />
This platform sought to <strong>connect those who were looking for fashion advice</strong> (aka don‚Äôt know how to dress, which may or may not include me) <strong>with stylish people who love giving fashion advice.</strong></p>

<p>The goal behind this was to fuel the <a href="https://a16z.com/2019/10/08/passion-economy/" target="_blank"> passion economy</a>.</p>

<p>I wanted to help people better monetise interests and skills that I believe are valuable, but haven‚Äôt been traditionally seen as such.</p>

<p>In this case, the value of having fashion sense. People pay for advice all the time - why shouldn‚Äôt those with fashion sense be able to profit as well?
<br /><br /></p>

<p><a href="https://lookgoodr.herokuapp.com/" target="_blank">
    <img src="http://localhost:4000/assets/lookgoodr/analytics.PNG" />
</a></p>
<h6>truly incredible 0% conversion</h6>
<p><br /></p>

<p><strong>Mistake 1: Fundamentally misunderstanding the problem</strong></p>

<p>Turns out that this isn‚Äôt that big a problem, or at least the target market was very narrow.</p>

<p>Those who care about dressing better would probably be actively searching for ways to do such, either through friends or the million reddit threads out there on the topic.</p>

<p>Those who don‚Äôt care about style - well, they wouldn‚Äôt pay money for this anyway.</p>

<p><strong>Mistake 2: Not understanding the buyer</strong></p>

<p>We initially targeted students/fresh grads in tech who wore hoodies during their entire undergrad and now have money to spend on clothes.</p>

<p>This decision was made (mostly by me) despite the fact that nobody from this demographic actually expressed a huge desire to dress better; it was always a: ‚Äúsure, I‚Äôd <em>probably</em> want to‚Äù - but who doesn‚Äôt?</p>

<p>**Mistake 3:</p>

